annotationA: Kinase; Inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate 6-kinase activity; inositol-1,4,5-trisphosphate 3-kinase activity; inositol tetrakisphosphate 5-kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: positive regulation of JAK-STAT cascade; inositol phosphate biosynthetic process; Belongs to the inositol phosphokinase (IPK) family
annotationB: Inositol-pentakisphosphate 2-kinase; Phosphorylates Ins(1,3,4,5,6)P5 at position 2 to form Ins(1,2,3,4,5,6)P6 (InsP6 or phytate)
